Design patterns are proven solution templates for recurring design problems in architecture as well as in software development.

A design pattern usually contains several classes (templates), so a single design pattern is a collection of different templates. E.g. The shape of a single step of stairs AND the railing (steelwork or eg woodwork) for the complete stairs AND for example the shape for the carpet of each step
